Sergeant Thabisile Phenelope Zondi 41 who worked at the Plessislaer police station died on Saturday morning.Police said the two had an argument at Zondi s home in Scottsville where she was assaulted with a pick handle. She suffered injuries to her body and face.She succumbed to the injuries and died on the scene. Her swollen body was found in a pool of blood with multiple injuries to the face.A case of murder was opened at Alexander Police Station and a suspect was eventually arrested. He will appear in court on Monday facing charges of murder.Acting Provincial Commissioner Major General Bheki Langa said he was shocked by the killing.- TMG Digital/Sunday Times